This paper deals with the problem of online bipartite matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of various algorithms and their analysis, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT).
